                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1112/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-04T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 4, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>396. My 395, October 3, 6 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Morrison calls my attention to an item in the French press to the effect
                        that French in full agreement with the British had worked out a project to
                        present in the League Second Committee. He does not believe that the French
                        Government inspired this but that it was simply an erroneous rumor. He said
                        that in any event it was completely untrue and that they were not working on
                        anything with the French and that the British position remained precisely as
                        he had described it to me.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Please instruct whether I should inform Paris and London of my
                        conversations with Spinasse and Morrison.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
